  "description": "<div>\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201507/599582b8c36244068c75a60a48f6f260.jpg\" width=\"100%/\" /></div>\n<div>\n\t&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201507/79ab3cd61ccc4145ad438abafb4f87bd.jpg\" /></div>\n<div>\n\t&nbsp;</div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t<strong>今日短语</strong></div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\tSnowed under 这个短语其实和&ldquo;snow 雪&rdquo;并没有什么关系。在英语里，人们常用这个表达来形容&ldquo;忙得不可开交&rdquo;。</div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t&nbsp;</div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t<strong>例句</strong></div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t<em>I'm sorry, I can't write that report for you right now - I'm snowed under with work today.</em></div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t<em>I'm going to treat myself to a spa weekend. I've been so snowed under lately; I need some time to relax.</em></div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t<em><br />\n\t</em></div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t<strong>请注意</strong></div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t另一个同单词 &ldquo;snow 雪&rdquo;有关的短语是 snowed in，意思是&ldquo;大雪封门，被困在家里&rdquo;。</div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t<em>Wendy rang to say that she can't come for dinner tonight &ndash; she's snowed in.</em></div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t&nbsp;</div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t<strong>今日小常识</strong></div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t&nbsp;</div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\tThe word 'ski' originated from the Old Norse word 'sk&iacute;e' which means 'split piece of wood or firewood'. Old Norse belongs to the North Germanic language which was spoken by people who lived in Scandinavia during the Viking Age.</div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t英语单词 ski 来源于古诺尔斯语单词&ldquo;sk&iacute;e&rdquo;，意思是&ldquo;一块木头或柴火&rdquo;。古诺尔斯语是维京时期居住在斯堪地纳维亚居民使用的语言。</div>\n<div>\n\t&nbsp;</div>\n<div id=\"cke_pastebin\">\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201507/ed2872d36cdf49faab64c11ed5df5609.jpg\" width=\"100%/\" /></div>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p740271/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"